  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/6496",
  "title": "Support for React 19 and Next 15",
  "body": "### 🐛 Current behavior\n\nwhen I upgrade to React 19 and Nextjs 15 then Reacts-instantsearch-next.js and and react-instantsearch are not compatible which has proven true in that I can run them in dev but not able to deploy to production. These are the last two components in the way of me completing the upgrade: Here is the message:\r\nYou may have to update these packages to their latest version or file an issue to ask for support of the upgraded libraries.\r\n\r\nreact-instantsearch 7.13.9\r\n  ├── ✕ unmet peer react@\">= 16.8.0 < 19\": found 19.0.0\r\n  └── ✕ unmet peer react-dom@\">= 16.8.0 < 19\": found 19.0.0\r\nreact-instantsearch-nextjs 0.3.20\r\n  └── ✕ unmet peer next@\">= 13.4 < 15\": found 15.1.2\r\n\r\n\r\nPlease review the local changes and read the Next.js 15 migration guide to complete the migration.\r\nhttps://nextjs.org/docs/canary/app/building-your-application/upgrading/version-15\n\n### 🔍 Steps to reproduce\n\ni used the code mod npx @next/codemod@canary upgrade latest\n\n### Live reproduction\n\nhttps://ibikeride.com/search\n\n### 💭 Expected behavior\n\nI should be able to use both these components and deploy to production without compatibility errors as they are not supported on React 19 \r\n  \"react-instantsearch\": \"^7.13.9\",\r\n    \"react-instantsearch-nextjs\": \"^0.3.20\",\n\n### Package version\n\n\"react-instantsearch\": \"^7.13.9\",   \"react-instantsearch-nextjs\": \"^0.3.20\",\n\n### Operating system\n\nmacOS Sonata \n\n### Browser\n\nMicrosoft Edge Version 131.0.2903.112 (Official build) (arm64)\n\n### Code of Conduct\n\n- [X] I agree to follow this project's Code of Conduct",
